\chapter{SYSTEM ANALYSIS}

\section{Existing System}

The existing approach to managing customer interactions across social media platforms is largely manual, fragmented, and inefficient. Businesses and content creators rely on individual platform dashboards such as Instagram, Facebook, and YouTube to monitor and respond to user comments. As the number of users and platforms increases, handling interactions becomes increasingly complex and time-consuming.

Currently, most organizations depend on human operators or social media managers to continuously monitor comments, reply to customer queries, and maintain engagement. This traditional approach is not only resource-intensive but also prone to errors and delays.

This leads to several critical challenges:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{High Manual Effort:} Users must frequently switch between multiple platforms to check comments and respond individually. This repetitive process consumes significant time and human resources, especially for businesses handling thousands of interactions daily.
    
    \item \textbf{Lack of Centralization:} There is no unified system to aggregate comments from multiple platforms. As a result, important messages may be overlooked, and tracking user interactions becomes difficult.
    
    \item \textbf{Delayed Response Time:} Manual handling causes delays in responding to customer queries, particularly outside working hours. This negatively impacts user satisfaction and reduces engagement rates.
    
    \item \textbf{Inconsistent Responses:} Replies depend on the individual handling the account, leading to variations in tone, language, and accuracy. This inconsistency can harm brand identity and professionalism.
    
    \item \textbf{Limited Automation:} Existing tools primarily rely on keyword-based auto-replies. These systems lack contextual understanding and fail to address user queries effectively, often resulting in irrelevant or generic responses.
    
    \item \textbf{No Intelligent Insights:} Traditional systems do not provide advanced analytics such as sentiment analysis, trend detection, or customer behavior insights, limiting strategic decision-making.
    
    \item \textbf{Scalability Issues:} As the number of users and interactions increases, manual systems fail to scale efficiently, leading to bottlenecks and reduced performance.
    
    \item \textbf{Risk of Human Error:} Important comments may be missed or incorrectly handled, affecting customer trust and business reputation.
\end{itemize}

These limitations result in poor customer engagement, missed business opportunities, inefficient resource utilization, and an overall decline in service quality.

\section{Proposed System}

To address the limitations of the existing system, the proposed solution, \textbf{RevAI}, is designed as an intelligent, automated, and centralized platform. It integrates modern web technologies, cloud databases, workflow automation, and advanced artificial intelligence to provide a seamless solution for social media management.

RevAI focuses on reducing manual workload, improving response quality, and enabling real-time insights through automation and AI-driven processing.

\subsection{Key Components}

The system is composed of the following major components:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Frontend (User Interface):}  
    The frontend is a web-based dashboard built using modern frameworks such as Next.js. It provides an intuitive interface where users can register, log in, connect their social media accounts using OAuth 2.0, and configure system settings such as reply tone, filters, and automation preferences. The UI is designed to be user-friendly, ensuring accessibility for both technical and non-technical users.
    
    \item \textbf{Backend (API Layer):}  
    The backend acts as the central control unit of the system. It handles user authentication, API communication, token management, and request processing. It also ensures secure interaction between the frontend, databases, and external APIs. The backend is responsible for enforcing business logic and maintaining system integrity.
    
    \item \textbf{Databases:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{PostgreSQL:} A relational database used to store structured and critical data such as user credentials, encrypted API tokens, platform connection details, and system configurations. It ensures data consistency and security.
        
        \item \textbf{Firebase Firestore:} A NoSQL database used to store unstructured and high-volume data such as comments, AI-generated replies, processing status, and reports. It provides scalability and real-time synchronization capabilities.
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Workflow Orchestration (Apache Airflow):}  
    Apache Airflow is used to automate and manage workflows through Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs). It schedules tasks such as fetching comments, processing them using AI, and posting replies at predefined intervals. Airflow ensures reliability by supporting retries, logging, and monitoring.
    
    \item \textbf{AI Engine (Gemini API):}  
    The AI engine leverages advanced Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to analyze user comments. It classifies comments based on intent (e.g., query, complaint, spam) and generates context-aware, human-like responses. This significantly enhances user engagement and response quality.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Advantages of Proposed System}

The proposed system offers several advantages over traditional approaches:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Automation:} Eliminates the need for manual monitoring and replying, significantly reducing human effort and operational costs.
    
    \item \textbf{Centralization:} Provides a unified dashboard where all comments from different platforms are managed in one place.
    
    \item \textbf{Scalability:} Designed to handle large volumes of data and users efficiently, making it suitable for both small businesses and large enterprises.
    
    \item \textbf{Intelligent Responses:} Uses AI to generate meaningful, context-aware replies instead of generic responses, improving customer satisfaction.
    
    \item \textbf{Reliability:} Airflow-based scheduling ensures tasks are executed consistently, with retry mechanisms for handling failures.
    
    \item \textbf{Real-Time Insights:} Enables analysis of customer sentiment, trends, and behavior, helping businesses make data-driven decisions.
    
    \item \textbf{Improved Customer Engagement:} Faster and more accurate responses lead to better interaction and increased user trust.
    
    \item \textbf{Enhanced Security:} Sensitive data such as API tokens are encrypted, ensuring secure system operations.
\end{itemize}

