\section{Data Flow Diagram}

The system processes data in multiple stages, including user interaction, data ingestion, processing, and automated response generation.

\subsection{User Registration and Platform Connection}

\begin{itemize}
    \item The user registers and logs into the system through the frontend interface.
    \item Authentication is handled securely using NextAuth.
    \item The system uses OAuth 2.0 to connect social media platforms such as YouTube and Instagram.
    \item Access tokens received are encrypted using AES-256 encryption.
    \item Encrypted tokens are stored securely in PostgreSQL.
    \item The user selects specific content (videos or posts) to monitor.
\end{itemize}



\subsection{Automated Comment Processing Workflow}

\begin{itemize}
    \item Apache Airflow schedules tasks at regular intervals.
    \item Comments are fetched from connected platforms using APIs.
    \item Retrieved comments are stored in Firestore with status \textit{pending}.
    \item The AI engine analyzes comments to determine intent and sentiment.
    \item Context-aware replies are generated automatically.
    \item Replies are posted back to the respective platforms.
    \item The comment status is updated to \textit{replied}.
\end{itemize}
