\chapter{Challenges and Limitations}

\section{Introduction}

During the development and implementation of the RevAI system, multiple technical and practical challenges were encountered. Since the system integrates modern web technologies, artificial intelligence models, third-party APIs, and workflow automation tools, several issues arose at different stages of development. 

This chapter highlights the major challenges faced during the project, including API integration difficulties, system design constraints, performance issues, and real-world limitations. Understanding these challenges is important as it reflects the complexity of building an end-to-end intelligent automation system.

\section{Challenges in Third-Party API Integration}

One of the most significant challenges faced in this project was integrating third-party platforms such as Instagram, Facebook, and Reddit.

\subsection{Instagram and Facebook Integration Issues}

Although the system architecture and pipeline for handling Instagram and Facebook comments were successfully designed, actual integration could not be fully completed due to the following reasons:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Strict API Permissions}: Meta (Facebook and Instagram) APIs require advanced permissions such as \texttt{instagram\_manage\_comments} and \texttt{pages\_manage\_metadata}, which are not easily granted without app review.
    
    \item \textbf{Business Account Requirement}: Instagram APIs only work with Business or Creator accounts linked to a Facebook page. This added additional setup complexity.
    
    \item \textbf{App Review Process}: Meta requires a detailed app review process, including video demonstrations and verification, which could not be completed within the project timeline.
    
    \item \textbf{Limited Testing Environment}: Even in development mode, only test users can access the API, limiting real-world testing.
    
    \item \textbf{Frequent API Changes}: Meta APIs are frequently updated, which leads to compatibility issues and breaking changes in implementation.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Reddit Integration Challenges}

Reddit integration was also attempted but faced several limitations:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Rate Limits}: Reddit imposes strict rate limits, restricting the number of API requests within a short time.
    
    \item \textbf{Authentication Complexity}: OAuth implementation for Reddit requires multiple steps and proper token handling, increasing development complexity.
    
    \item \textbf{Limited Write Access}: Posting automated replies is restricted and requires special permissions, making automation difficult.
    
    \item \textbf{Inconsistent Data Structure}: Comment structures vary across threads, making parsing and processing more complex.
\end{itemize}

\section{Challenges in AI Integration}

Integrating the Artificial Intelligence Model for classification and reply generation also introduced several challenges:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{API Dependency}: The system relies on external AI services, which can fail due to network issues or API downtime.
    
    \item \textbf{Response Latency}: Generating responses using AI introduces delay, especially when processing large batches of comments.
    
    \item \textbf{Prompt Engineering}: Designing effective prompts to generate meaningful and context-aware replies required multiple iterations and testing.
    
    \item \textbf{Inconsistent Outputs}: AI-generated responses may sometimes be irrelevant, repetitive, or not aligned with user expectations.
    
    \item \textbf{Cost Constraints}: Frequent API calls for classification and reply generation can increase operational cost in real-world deployment.
\end{itemize}

\section{Challenges in Workflow Automation (Airflow)}

While Apache Airflow enabled automation of the pipeline, it introduced its own set of challenges:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{DAG Debugging Complexity}: Debugging DAG failures required analyzing logs and understanding task dependencies, which was time-consuming.
    
    \item \textbf{Environment Configuration}: Setting up Airflow using Docker required proper configuration of environment variables and services like Redis and PostgreSQL.
    
    \item \textbf{Task Synchronization Issues}: Ensuring smooth data flow between fetching, processing, and posting DAGs was challenging.
    
    \item \textbf{Handling Failures}: Proper retry mechanisms and failure handling had to be implemented to avoid data inconsistency.
\end{itemize}

\section{Database Management Challenges}

The system uses both PostgreSQL and Firestore, which created certain complexities:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Dual Database Handling}: Managing structured and unstructured data across two databases increased system complexity.
    
    \item \textbf{Data Synchronization}: Keeping data consistent between databases during updates was challenging.
    
    \item \textbf{Query Optimization}: Efficient querying of large volumes of comments required careful design.
\end{itemize}

\section{Security and Authentication Challenges}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Token Encryption}: Securely storing and decrypting OAuth tokens required careful implementation using encryption techniques.
    
    \item \textbf{OAuth Errors}: Issues like redirect URI mismatch and expired tokens frequently occurred during integration.
    
    \item \textbf{Session Handling}: Maintaining secure user sessions across the application required proper configuration.
\end{itemize}

\section{Performance and Scalability Limitations}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{API Rate Limits}: Platforms like YouTube and Reddit limit API usage, affecting scalability.
    
    \item \textbf{Processing Delay}: Large volumes of comments increase processing time in the pipeline.
    
    \item \textbf{System Load}: Running multiple services (Airflow, database, frontend) locally requires high system resources.
\end{itemize}

\section{Development Constraints}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Time Limitation}: The project was developed within a limited timeframe, restricting full feature implementation.
    
    \item \textbf{API Restrictions}: Many features depend on third-party APIs, which limited flexibility.
    
    \item \textbf{Testing Limitations}: Real-world testing was limited due to lack of production-level API access.
\end{itemize}

\section{Summary}

The development of the RevAI system involved overcoming multiple challenges across API integration, AI processing, workflow automation, and system design. While several features were successfully implemented, certain limitations such as restricted API access, dependency on external services, and system complexity impacted the full realization of the system. These challenges provide valuable insights into building scalable and real-world AI-driven automation systems.

